snippet.textDisplay: “21 Years” is a song I wrote about the recent passing of my firstborn son, Truett Foster McKeehan. I loved him with all my heart. Until something in life hits you this hard, you never know how you will handle it. I am thankful that I have been surrounded by love, starting with God’s and extending to community near and far that have walked with us and carried us every day. Writing this song felt like an honest confession of the questions, pain, anger, doubt, mercy and promise that describes the journey I’m probably only beginning. The rest is yet to come. One thing I know is that I am not alone. God didn’t promise us a life of no pain or even tragic death, but He did promise He would never leave us or forsake us. And I’m holding dearly to that promise for my son as well as myself.

snippet.textDisplay: Toby, as I heard your sound I saw myself and my family surround you, sing over you....you are not alone and this attempt by the enemy has come as a distraction and an attempt to stop you.  What were you working on when this happened?  I feel compelled to ask.  I see a double portion- he was working on something and so were you- a new song- a duet of revelation.  You will find it my brother when the pain lessens and you can breathe again.  Our prayers are with you.  YOU SAVED THE LIFE OF MY OLDEST DAUGHTER with your sound- it reverberates throughout the earth and crumbles the high places spoken of by God and called by the Father to the prophet Jeremiah to tear down the high places.  Your sound tears down strongholds constructed by the enemy- don't stop- now your boy sings with you amidst your cloud of witnesses and he understands the battle that is before you.  The enemy thought he had you, but now, your son will sing a duet with his savior...with you too.  There is something coming that will rightly align this new generation whose identity has been crushed- you have it already.  You have the words and now the sound comes!  God bless you in your righteous anger- you were robbed, but Gow will use it all as you well know...an undisclosed ember burns my brother- your mantel will pass to another.

snippet.textDisplay: TobyMac... I can't even start to think about how terrible this is. We all know how much you deeply cared for your son. From the beginning of his young age you guys would jam out to music and sing together. For this to happen is the most tragic thing in the world. But we all know that God is the one and only one who knows what's going to happen and why. We all know that the Lord is not cruel for taking Tru. I also know losing someone you very deeply care about is the worst feeling anyone could ever feel. I lost my aunt when I was 3. I thought that was the worst thing ever. But here you are, you lost your first born child who you so deeply loved. I can't comprehend that this has happened, and I'm sure you can't either. And you are correct, you are not alone. God is with you, your family is with you, and all of us out here supporting you are here for you. We are all praying our hearts out for you and your family. We are all praying that Tru is smiling at Home with the amazing God. God did make the promise to never leave us or forsake us, therefore even though this is one of the worst tragedy's to happen to you; we need to remember that God has a reason for everything. Wether we like or not we have to follow and obey what God has to say and do. We are all here for you Toby. We are praying for you and your family and sending you guys all of our love. I pray you have a blessed life. And remember, Tru is with you. Maybe not physically, but emotionally and spiritually. He loved you more than he could ever say. Prayers sent now and forever. :)) <3

snippet.textDisplay: T - as a father I have thought about your loss the past couple months.  In fact the night I heard, I spent time watching my 4yr old son as he slept, praying for him, praying for you, and thanking God for him.  My wife and I teared up when we heard the terrible news and then we smiled and talked about all the "intros" and "outros" T-Dog was on in your albums - he touched our lives, and we never knew him.  We looked forward to hearing each new intro and outro with each new album you put out.  And know our little ones love to listen to "TodyMac" as they call you.  They are 3 and 4 and your music, your testimony has touched my kids everyday in the car to and from daycare and church.  We have you on our Pandora and listen often.  Stay strong, much love and heartfelt prayers for you and your family!
snippet.textOriginal: T - as a father I have thought about your loss the past couple months. More power to you ! 21 years is a special song that is dwelling deep in our hearts.
Love to you from India, I'm 21years old and trust me all your quotes are the ones which made my teenage strong. God talks thru your quotes. Tobymac quotes are our daily dose of God's word which touches our soul. I'm so in love with the way you got deep in to Jesus after losing your son. You are a blessing to our generation and a true inspiration !! Please know that we are fighting the world with God and thru inspiration drawn thru ppl like you who take us close to God day by day. You are a true spiritual father !! We love you ! Stay strong 💪

snippet.textDisplay: A beautiful heartfelt song. I think this is a parent's greatest fear and you can only make it by God's grace and leaning fully on His unwavering love for you. We don't always understand His ways but His ways are right. I pray the Lord continues to give you and your family the strength that only He can provide. Thank you for standing in such a difficult and unimaginable time. Only a true believer in Christ can still see His love and this helps us all it is such encouragement to the Believer. God bless you as you continue on the path He has set for you. Wow! Amazing tribute to your son. Thanks for sharing such a personal experience like that with us!
